# Email Configuration for Contact Form
# To enable automatic email sending, copy this file to .env and fill in your credentials

# Mailgun Configuration (Recommended)
MAILGUN_API_KEY=your-mailgun-api-key
MAILGUN_DOMAIN=your-domain-here

# DOMAIN OPTIONS:
# Option 1 - Sandbox (Testing): sandbox123abc.mailgun.org
# Option 2 - Your Domain (Production): yourdomain.com
# Option 3 - Subdomain (Recommended): mail.yourdomain.com

# CURRENT SETUP EXAMPLES:
# For testing (sandbox):
# MAILGUN_DOMAIN=sandbox35e13be1d96a4562b4e2444c7760dd39.mailgun.org

# For your own domain:
# MAILGUN_DOMAIN=paulmallner.com
# MAILGUN_DOMAIN=mail.paulmallner.com

# Mailgun Setup Instructions:
# 1. Sign up for free at https://www.mailgun.com/
# 2. Verify your account (may require phone verification)
# 3. Go to Dashboard > Sending > Domains
# 4. For testing: Use sandbox domain (emails from noreply@sandbox...)
# 5. For production: Add your own domain (emails from contact@yourdomain.com)
# 6. Go to Dashboard > Settings > API Keys
# 7. Copy your Private API key (starts with key-...)
# 8. Fill in the values above and restart the server

# Adding Your Own Domain:
# 1. In Mailgun Dashboard, click "Add New Domain"
# 2. Enter your domain (e.g., paulmallner.com)
# 3. Add the DNS records Mailgun provides to your domain
# 4. Wait for verification (can take up to 48 hours)
# 5. Update MAILGUN_DOMAIN above with your verified domain

# Mailgun Free Tier:
# - 5,000 emails/month for first 3 months
# - 1,000 emails/month after that
# - Sandbox: Limited to 5 authorized recipients
# - Own domain: No recipient restrictions